HEADWORD: Creepy
<hw>Creep"y</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧p"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Crawly;
having or producing a sensation like that caused by insects creeping on
the skin.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One's whole blood grew curdling and <qex>creepy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>R. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

